Veteran Actor, Yemi Solade has taken to his official social media handle to celebrate his daughter who just gained admission into the University. Kofoworola Solade just gained admission into Caleb University.
The actor reposted his wife’s post and said, “Congratulations to my daughter in whom I’m well pleased”.
Yemi Solade’s wife, Hannah Marsh Solade pens down lovely notes as she celebrates her daughter. She said education is the passport to the future and tomorrow belongs to those who prepare for it today.
She said she should be ready to build her life and career with varieties of questions and difficulties thrown at her in the course of her program and prayed that her expectation for excellence will not be cut short.
Hannah said her family counts themselves lucky to have invested in her admission adding that they did not lose because her diligence motivates them to contribute more to her successful academic career.

In conclusion, she said, “There is no substitute for hard work. You made it! Now, aspire to inspire before you expire. Happy matriculation”.
This good news sparked reactions online as fans and celebrities sent congratulatory messages.



